  • Constructor Details

    • DialogOption

      private DialogOption(String buttonText, char buttonMnemonic, String secondaryButtonText, String buttonIcon, int numButtons, int defaultButton)
      Dialog option types constructor
      Parameters:
      buttonText - Text to display on the primary button
      buttonMnemonic - Character for actuating the primary button via the keyboard
      secondaryButtonText - Text to display on the secondary button (if present)
      buttonIcon - Identifier for the icon to display on the primary button
      numButtons - Number of buttons to display in the dialog
      defaultButton - Index of the button selected by default

    • DialogOption

      private DialogOption(CcddConstants.DialogOption[] options)
      Dialog option types constructor
      Parameters:
      options - [] An array containing a set of dialog buttons to create in in order. "this" dialog option will be defaulted and not used

    • DialogOption

      private DialogOption(String buttonText, char buttonMnemonic, String secondaryButtonText, String buttonIcon, int numButtons, int defaultButton, int buttonType)
      Dialog option types constructor
      Parameters:
      buttonText - Text to display on the primary button
      buttonMnemonic - Character for actuating the primary button via the keyboard
      secondaryButtonText - Text to display on the secondary button (if present)
      buttonIcon - Identifier for the icon to display on the primary button
      numButtons - Number of buttons to display in the dialog
      defaultButton - Index of the button selected by default
      buttonType - Chosen button associated with this option. For example[OK, CANCEL, UPDATE, IGNORE]

    • DialogOption

      private DialogOption(String buttonText, char buttonMnemonic, String secondaryButtonText, String buttonIcon, int numButtons, int defaultButton, int buttonType, CcddConstants.DialogOption[] options)
      Dialog option types constructor
      Parameters:
      buttonText - Text to display on the primary button
      buttonMnemonic - Character for actuating the primary button via the keyboard
      secondaryButtonText - Text to display on the secondary button (if present)
      buttonIcon - Identifier for the icon to display on the primary button
      numButtons - Number of buttons to display in the dialog
      defaultButton - Index of the button selected by default
      buttonType - Chosen button associated with this option. For example[OK, CANCEL, UPDATE, IGNORE]
      options - [] An array containing other dialog buttons to create in order
